Perfect, this is a code-level fix ğŸ‘
Below is the revised and correct getSupportingDocsByPipId (aka getSupportingDocsByReportId) method for your scenario.

This version:
	â€¢	âœ… Correctly queries the SupportingDocumentations library
	â€¢	âœ… Filters by PerformanceParentPIPID
	â€¢	âœ… Returns plain array
	â€¢	âœ… Works for edit draft reload
