â¸»

ğŸ”´ Root cause (very important)

1ï¸âƒ£ File inputs can NEVER be prefilled

This is a browser security rule.

So this will never work (and should not work):

<input type="file" ... />

When you reopen a draft, the browser will NOT show test.pdf inside the file chooser even if:
	â€¢	The file exists in SharePoint âœ…
	â€¢	Parent ID is correct âœ…
	â€¢	Metadata is correct âœ…

ğŸ‘‰ This is expected behavior. Not a bug.

â¸»

ğŸŸ¢ What SHOULD happen instead (correct UX)

When reopening the draft:
	â€¢	âŒ You do NOT show the file inside <input type="file">
	â€¢	âœ… You SHOW a list of already uploaded documents
	â€¢	âœ… You optionally allow:
	â€¢	Download
	â€¢	View
	â€¢	Delete
	â€¢	Upload another file

This is exactly how SharePoint, Jira, ServiceNow, etc. behave.

â¸»

âœ… What you already did right (important)

From your screenshots/code, you already have:

âœ” File uploaded
âœ” PerformanceParentPIPID patched
âœ” Library contains the file
âœ” Metadata column exists
âœ” getSupportingDocsByReportId() implemented

So backend = DONE âœ”

â¸»

âŒ Why you donâ€™t â€œseeâ€ the PDF when editing

Because currently:
	â€¢	You never bind the fetched docs to the UI
	â€¢	You expect the file input to show the file (impossible)

â¸»

âœ… THE FIX (this will solve everything)

