â¸»

1ï¸âƒ£ Why this is happening (root cause)

ğŸ”´ The real culprit: getValidPerformanceIssues()

You have this method:

private getValidPerformanceIssues(raw: any[]): any[] {
  return raw
    .filter(issue =>
      issue.timeline &&
      issue.issue?.trim() &&
      issue.standard?.trim() &&
      issue.currentAssessment?.trim()
    )
    .map(issue => ({
      ...issue,
      timeline: this.displayToIso(issue.timeline)
    }));
}

What this means in plain English

A performance issue row is considered â€œvalidâ€ ONLY IF:
	â€¢	timeline âœ…
	â€¢	issue text âœ…
	â€¢	standard âœ…
	â€¢	currentAssessment âœ…

If even one field is missing, that row is silently dropped.

â¸»

2ï¸âƒ£ Why Draft save fails when only â€œPerformance Issueâ€ is filled

Step-by-step what actually happens

When you click Save as Draft:
