Got it ğŸ‘ I can see the issue clearly.

Your table content is left-aligned by default, so even though the table itself is fine, the text inside <th> and <td> isnâ€™t centered.

âœ… Minimal change (CSS-only, safest fix)

Just add text-align: center to your table cells.

Option 1: Inline (absolute minimum change)
Change your header and row HTML like this:

<th style="padding:4px 8px; text-align:center;">Date</th>
<th style="padding:4px 8px; text-align:center;">Start</th>
<th style="padding:4px 8px; text-align:center;">End</th>

And in row creation:

<td style="text-align:center;">${dateStr}</td>
<td style="text-align:center;">${startStr}</td>
<td style="text-align:center;">${endStr}</td>


â¸»

âœ… Cleaner minimal change (recommended)

Since you already have a class session-table, add just this CSS once:

.session-table th,
.session-table td {
  text-align: center;
}

ğŸ‘‰ Thatâ€™s it. Nothing else needed.

â¸»

Why this works
	â€¢	Your table layout is correct
	â€¢	Columns are aligned
	â€¢	Only the content alignment was missing
	â€¢	This fix doesnâ€™t affect spacing, width, or structure

If you want, next we can:
	â€¢	Vertically center (vertical-align: middle)
	â€¢	Match Outlook email styling
	â€¢	Fix mobile responsiveness

