This is a very common AG-Grid + PrimeNG pitfall ğŸ‘
Nothing is wrong with your styles.css.

âŒ Root cause (IMPORTANT)

You are rendering PrimeNG buttons (pButton, pi pi-eye) as raw HTML strings inside:

cellRenderer: (params) => ` <button pButton icon="pi pi-eye"> `

â¡ï¸ Angular does NOT compile directives inside AG-Grid string renderers
So:
	â€¢	pButton âŒ ignored
	â€¢	pi pi-eye âŒ not applied
	â€¢	Result = small blank dashes (what you see now)

â¸»

âœ… WHY ICONS ARE NOT VISIBLE

Thing	Reason
PrimeIcons CSS	âœ… loaded (correct)
PrimeNG Button	âŒ not compiled
pButton	âŒ Angular directive
AG-Grid cellRenderer	âŒ plain DOM only

ğŸ‘‰ PrimeNG components will NEVER work inside string HTML

â¸»

âœ… CORRECT FIX (2 WORKING OPTIONS)

â¸»

âœ… OPTION 1 (FAST & RECOMMENDED): Use PrimeIcons ONLY (no pButton)

ğŸ”¹ Change your Action column renderer to this ğŸ‘‡

cellRenderer: (params: any) => {
  const isClosed = ['closed', 'submitted'].includes(
    (params.data.Status || '').toLowerCase()
  );

  const id = params.data.Id;

  const viewIcon = `
    <span class="pi pi-eye action-icon view" data-id="${id}" title="View"></span>
  `;

  const editIcon = isClosed
    ? ''
    : `
      <span class="pi pi-pencil action-icon edit" data-id="${id}" title="Edit"></span>
    `;

  return `<div class="action-wrapper">${viewIcon}${editIcon}</div>`;
};


â¸»

ğŸ”¹ Add THIS CSS (THIS makes it look like your 3rd image)

.action-wrapper {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 14px;
}

.action-icon {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  cursor: pointer;
  color: rgba(0,145,90,1);
  transition: transform 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
}

.action-icon:hover {
  transform: scale(1.2);
  color: rgba(0,120,75,1);
}

âœ… Icons WILL appear immediately

