Good catch â€” this error is 100% Angular setup + event binding, not your logic. Letâ€™s fix it cleanly.

â¸»

âŒ Why this error is happening

You are using <p-dropdown> (PrimeNG) but:

1ï¸âƒ£ [options] error

Angular says:

Canâ€™t bind to options since it isnâ€™t a known property of p-dropdown

ğŸ‘‰ Meaning: PrimeNG DropdownModule is NOT imported in this component.

â¸»

2ï¸âƒ£ (onChange)="onEmployeeSelected($event.value)" error

Angular says:

Property value does not exist on type Event

ğŸ‘‰ Because PrimeNG emits a custom event, not a normal DOM event.

â¸»

âœ… FIX STEP BY STEP

â¸»

âœ… STEP 1: Import DropdownModule properly

If your component is standalone (Angular 15+)

In pipform.component.ts:

import { DropdownModule } from 'primeng/dropdown';
import { ReactiveFormsModule } from '@angular/forms';

Then in @Component:

@Component({
  selector: 'app-pipform',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [
    ReactiveFormsModule,
    DropdownModule
  ],
  templateUrl: './pipform.component.html'
})


â¸»

If NOT standalone (NgModule based)

In your module (app.module.ts or feature module):

import { DropdownModule } from 'primeng/dropdown';

@NgModule({
  imports: [
    ReactiveFormsModule,
    DropdownModule
  ]
})
export class AppModule {}


