Good, this screenshot finally shows the real blocker ğŸ‘
Donâ€™t worry â€” this is NOT a SharePoint / API problem.
Itâ€™s a Reactive Forms wiring mistake (very common).

â¸»

âŒ Your exact error (what it means)

Type 'AbstractControl<any, any> | null' is not assignable to type 'FormGroup<any>'

Error line:

<div class="grid" formGroupName="manager" [formGroup]="pipForm.get('manager')">

ğŸ”¥ Root cause

You are mixing two different approaches:
	â€¢	formGroupName="manager" âœ… (correct)
	â€¢	[formGroup]="pipForm.get('manager')" âŒ (WRONG here)

pipForm.get('manager') returns AbstractControl | null,
Angular expects FormGroup, so it crashes.

â¸»

âœ… RULE (remember this forever)

âœ” When using formGroupName

ğŸ‘‰ DO NOT use [formGroup]

âœ” When using [formGroup]

ğŸ‘‰ DO NOT use formGroupName

â¸»

âœ… Correct & WORKING solution (minimal change)

âœ” pipform.component.ts (ONLY what matters)

import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { FormBuilder, FormGroup, ReactiveFormsModule } from '@angular/forms';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { UserInfoService } from '../../services/sharepoint.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-pipform',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule, ReactiveFormsModule],
  templateUrl: './pipform.component.html'
})
export class PIPFormComponent implements OnInit {

  pipForm!: FormGroup;

  constructor(
    private fb: FormBuilder,
    private userInfo: UserInfoService
  ) {}

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.pipForm = this.fb.group({
      manager: this.fb.group({
        uid: [''],
        name: [''],
        email: ['']
      })
    });

    this.loadManager();
  }

  private loadManager(): void {
    this.userInfo.getManagerInfo().subscribe(info => {
      this.pipForm.patchValue({
        manager: {
          uid: info.uid,
          name: info.name,
          email: info.email
        }
      });

      this.pipForm.get('manager')?.disable(); // read-only
    });
  }
}


