Thanks for the image â€” it clearly shows AG Grid v33+ breaking changes, especially:

â¸»

âŒ Error Recap:

AG Grid: error #239 Theming API and CSS file themes are both used in the same page...

This happens because youâ€™re using old CSS (ag-theme-alpine.css) with AG Grid v33+, which now uses a new theming API.

â¸»

âœ… Fix the Issue Step-by-Step

âœ… Step 1: Remove old CSS import

Go to your app.component.ts and remove this line:

// âŒ REMOVE THIS
import 'ag-grid-community/styles/ag-theme-alpine.css';


â¸»

âœ… Step 2: Use new theme API in global styles.css (or styles.scss)

In your src/styles.css (or src/styles.scss), replace old CSS with:

@use "ag-grid-community/styles" as ag;

@include ag.grid-core();
@include ag.theme-alpine(); /* or any theme you prefer */

âœ… You need to make sure your project supports SCSS if using @use syntax.

If youâ€™re not using SCSS yet, rename styles.css â†’ styles.scss, then update angular.json to reflect that under styles.

â¸»

âœ… Step 3: Update Row Selection (no more string values)

In your app.component.ts, change:

// âŒ Old style (deprecated)
rowSelection="single"

To:

[rowSelection]="{ type: 'single' }"

Also:

// âŒ DEPRECATED: checkboxSelection: true
{ field: 'make', editable: true, checkboxSelection: true }

Change to:

{
  field: 'make',
  editable: true,
  headerCheckboxSelection: true,
  checkboxSelection: true
}

âš ï¸ But still be aware: checkbox selection support also changed in v33, and AG Grid recommends using new config format for multi-selection.

â¸»

ğŸ” Summary of Updated Fixes
	â€¢	âœ… Migrate to SCSS and use AG Gridâ€™s @use theming syntax
	â€¢	âœ… Avoid ag-theme-alpine.css import in TS
	â€¢	âœ… Use object format for row selection
	â€¢	âœ… Use updated grid configuration for checkbox selection

â¸»

ğŸ‘‡ Need help updating angular.json, styles.scss, or theming?

Let me know if:
	â€¢	You want to continue using CSS (then we disable new theme API)
	â€¢	Or you want help converting the project to SCSS
	â€¢	Or want to use a specific theme (like theme-balham, theme-material)

Iâ€™ll guide you based on what youâ€™re using.






